    range: "100 feet",
    area: "",
    duration: "until the end of your next turn",
    saving_throw: "",
    description: "With a whispered prayer or arcane sending, you conjure Arcanotheign, herald of Nethys. She's a storm of magic, half white and half black, roiling in a vaguely humanoid shape. She occupies the space of a Medium creature and has a Speed of 40 feet and a fly Speed of 60 feet.\n\nArrive (sonic) Storm's Unbridled Destruction Arcanotheign arrives with a flash of light and a cacophonous crash of colliding magic. All enemies in a 60-foot area take 8d12 sonic damage with a basic Reflex save. A creature that critically fails is additionally Deafened for 10 minutes.\n\nDepart (electricity, healing) Flash of Brilliance Arcanotheign fires a powerful arcane blast at one target within 100 feet, dealing 5d12 electricity damage with a basic Reflex save, and a powerful divine blast at one ally, healing 5d12 Hit Points. Then, Arcanotheign asks for payment in the form of a fond memory. If you pay this cost, you lose this memory, Arcanotheign gains this memory, and Arcanotheign whispers a secret into your mind; you can immediately Recall Knowledge on any subject at mythic proficiency.",
    heightened_effects: "[]",
